            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20promise%20of%20God's%20faithfulness%20to%20His%20own.%20All%20day-day%20in%2C%20day%20out%2C%20year%20in%2C%20and%20year%20out-God's%20faithfulness%20is%20great.%20Man%2C%20in%20his%20stubbornness%20and%20rebellion%2C%20may%20drift%20away%20from%20God%2C%20but%20through%20it%20all%2C%20%22He%20remains%20faithful%22%20(2%20Timothy%202%3A13).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ENo%20matter%20what%20difficulty%20life%20throws%20your%20way%2C%20God%20has%20promised%20to%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%22keep%20the%20temptation%20from%20becoming%20so%20strong%20that%20you%20can't%20stand%20up%20against%20it.%20When%20you%20are%20tempted%2C%20he%20will%20show%20you%20a%20way%20out%20so%20that%20you%20will%20not%20give%20in%20to%20it%22%20(1%20Corinthians%2010%3A13).%20David%20was%20so%20convinced%20of%20the%20faithfulness%20of%20God%20that%20he%20could%20say%2C%20%22Though%20a%20mighty%20army%20surrounds%20me%2C%20my%20heart%20will%20know%20no%20fear.%20Even%20if%20they%20attack%20me%2C%20I%20remain%20confident%22%20(Psalm%2027%3A3).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20God%20is%20faithful%20to%20execute%20His%20judgment%20upon%20those%20who%20reject%20Him%20even%20after%20He%20has%20repeatedly%20warned%20them%20to%20repent.%20Gradually%2C%20but%20surely%2C%20He%20tightens%20the%20screws%20of%20justice%20until%20the%20person%20repents%20or%20brings%20about%20his%20own%20destruction.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAs%20hard%20as%20it%20is%20to%20believe%2C%20some%20people%20actually%20do%20choose%20the%20path%20of%20destruction.%20In%202%20Chronicles%2036%3A13%2C%20we%20read%20that%20%22Zedekiah%20was%20a%20hard%20and%20stubborn%20man%2C%20refusing%20to%20turn%20to%20the%20Lord%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel.%22%20Following%20his%20example%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20grew%20more%20and%20more%20unfaithful%2C%20ignoring%20God's%20repeated%20warnings%20until%20finally%20%22the%20Lord's%20anger%20could%20no%20longer%20be%20restrained%20and%20there%20was%20no%20remedy%22%20(2%20Chronicles%2036%3A16).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIf%20life%20is%20uncertain%20right%20now%2C%20cling%20to%20the%20one%20certainty%3A%20God%20is%20faithful!%20You%20can%20be%20sure%20that%20%22He%20will%20keep%20you%20strong%20right%20up%20to%20the%20end%22%20(1%20Corinthians%201%3A8).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Chr.35:1-36:23",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Chronicles%2035%3A1-36%3A23%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E35%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJosiah%20Celebrates%20Passover%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Josiah%20announced%20that%20the%20Passover%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20would%20be%20celebrated%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20and%20so%20the%20Passover%20lamb%20was%20slaughtered%20on%20the%20fourteenth%20day%20of%20the%20first%20month.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E35%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20This%20day%20in%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20was%20April%26%23xA0%3B5%2C%20622%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EJosiah%20also%20assigned%20the%20priests%20to%20their%20duties%20and%20encouraged%20them%20in%20their%20work%20at%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20issued%20this%20order%20to%20the%20Levites%2C%20who%20were%20to%20teach%20all%20Israel%20and%20who%20had%20been%20set%20apart%20to%20serve%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BPut%20the%20holy%20Ark%20in%20the%20Temple%20that%20was%20built%20by%20Solomon%20son%20of%20David%2C%20the%20king%20of%20Israel.%20You%20no%20longer%20need%20to%20carry%20it%20back%20and%20forth%20on%20your%20shoulders.%20Now%20spend%20your%20time%20serving%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20and%20his%20people%20Israel.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EReport%20for%20duty%20according%20to%20the%20family%20divisions%20of%20your%20ancestors%2C%20following%20the%20directions%20of%20King%20David%20of%20Israel%20and%20the%20directions%20of%20his%20son%20Solomon.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThen%20stand%20in%20the%20sanctuary%20at%20the%20place%20appointed%20for%20your%20family%20division%20and%20help%20the%20families%20assigned%20to%20you%20as%20they%20bring%20their%20offerings%20to%20the%20Temple.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3ESlaughter%20the%20Passover%20lambs%2C%20purify%20yourselves%2C%20and%20prepare%20to%20help%20those%20who%20come.%20Follow%20all%20the%20directions%20that%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20gave%20through%20Moses.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Josiah%20provided%2030%2C000%20lambs%20and%20young%20goats%20for%20the%20people%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Passover%20offerings%2C%20along%20with%203%2C000%20cattle%2C%20all%20from%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20own%20flocks%20and%20herds.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20officials%20also%20made%20willing%20contributions%20to%20the%20people%2C%20priests%2C%20and%20Levites.%20Hilkiah%2C%20Zechariah%2C%20and%20Jehiel%2C%20the%20administrators%20of%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%2C%20gave%20the%20priests%202%2C600%20lambs%20and%20young%20goats%20and%20300%26%23xA0%3Bcattle%20as%20Passover%20offerings.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Levite%20leaders%26%23x2014%3BConaniah%20and%20his%20brothers%20Shemaiah%20and%20Nethanel%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Hashabiah%2C%20Jeiel%2C%20and%20Jozabad%26%23x2014%3Bgave%205%2C000%20lambs%20and%20young%20goats%20and%20500%26%23xA0%3Bcattle%20to%20the%20Levites%20for%20their%20Passover%20offerings.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20everything%20was%20ready%20for%20the%20Passover%20celebration%2C%20the%20priests%20and%20the%20Levites%20took%20their%20places%2C%20organized%20by%20their%20divisions%2C%20as%20the%20king%20had%20commanded.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Levites%20then%20slaughtered%20the%20Passover%20lambs%20and%20presented%20the%20blood%20to%20the%20priests%2C%20who%20sprinkled%20the%20blood%20on%20the%20altar%20while%20the%20Levites%20prepared%20the%20animals.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20divided%20the%20burnt%20offerings%20among%20the%20people%20by%20their%20family%20groups%2C%20so%20they%20could%20offer%20them%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20as%20prescribed%20in%20the%20Book%20of%20Moses.%20They%20did%20the%20same%20with%20the%20cattle.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20they%20roasted%20the%20Passover%20lambs%20as%20prescribed%3B%20and%20they%20boiled%20the%20holy%20offerings%20in%20pots%2C%20kettles%2C%20and%20pans%2C%20and%20brought%20them%20out%20quickly%20so%20the%20people%20could%20eat%20them.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EAfterward%20the%20Levites%20prepared%20Passover%20offerings%20for%20themselves%20and%20for%20the%20priests%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20descendants%20of%20Aaron%26%23x2014%3Bbecause%20the%20priests%20had%20been%20busy%20from%20morning%20till%20night%20offering%20the%20burnt%20offerings%20and%20the%20fat%20portions.%20The%20Levites%20took%20responsibility%20for%20all%20these%20preparations.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20musicians%2C%20descendants%20of%20Asaph%2C%20were%20in%20their%20assigned%20places%2C%20following%20the%20commands%20that%20had%20been%20given%20by%20David%2C%20Asaph%2C%20Heman%2C%20and%20Jeduthun%2C%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20seer.%20The%20gatekeepers%20guarded%20the%20gates%20and%20did%20not%20need%20to%20leave%20their%20posts%20of%20duty%2C%20for%20their%20Passover%20offerings%20were%20prepared%20for%20them%20by%20their%20fellow%20Levites.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20entire%20ceremony%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Passover%20was%20completed%20that%20day.%20All%20the%20burnt%20offerings%20were%20sacrificed%20on%20the%20altar%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20as%20King%20Josiah%20had%20commanded.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20the%20Israelites%20present%20in%20Jerusalem%20celebrated%20Passover%20and%20the%20Festival%20of%20Unleavened%20Bread%20for%20seven%20days.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3ENever%20since%20the%20time%20of%20the%20prophet%20Samuel%20had%20there%20been%20such%20a%20Passover.%20None%20of%20the%20kings%20of%20Israel%20had%20ever%20kept%20a%20Passover%20as%20Josiah%20did%2C%20involving%20all%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites%2C%20all%20the%20people%20of%20Jerusalem%2C%20and%20people%20from%20all%20over%20Judah%20and%20Israel.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20Passover%20was%20celebrated%20in%20the%20eighteenth%20year%20of%20Josiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_20%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJosiah%20Dies%20in%20Battle%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20Josiah%20had%20finished%20restoring%20the%20Temple%2C%20King%20Neco%20of%20Egypt%20led%20his%20army%20up%20from%20Egypt%20to%20do%20battle%20at%20Carchemish%20on%20the%20Euphrates%20River%2C%20and%20Josiah%20and%20his%20army%20marched%20out%20to%20fight%20him.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E35%3A20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EJosiah%20went%20out%20to%20meet%20him.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_21%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20King%20Neco%20sent%20messengers%20to%20Josiah%20with%20this%20message%3A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20do%20you%20want%20with%20me%2C%20king%20of%20Judah%3F%20I%20have%20no%20quarrel%20with%20you%20today!%20I%20am%20on%20my%20way%20to%20fight%20another%20nation%2C%20and%20God%20has%20told%20me%20to%20hurry!%20Do%20not%20interfere%20with%20God%2C%20who%20is%20with%20me%2C%20or%20he%20will%20destroy%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_22%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Josiah%20refused%20to%20listen%20to%20Neco%2C%20to%20whom%20God%20had%20indeed%20spoken%2C%20and%20he%20would%20not%20turn%20back.%20Instead%2C%20he%20disguised%20himself%20and%20led%20his%20army%20into%20battle%20on%20the%20plain%20of%20Megiddo.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_23%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20enemy%20archers%20hit%20King%20Josiah%20with%20their%20arrows%20and%20wounded%20him.%20He%20cried%20out%20to%20his%20men%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BTake%20me%20from%20the%20battle%2C%20for%20I%20am%20badly%20wounded!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_24%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20they%20lifted%20Josiah%20out%20of%20his%20chariot%20and%20placed%20him%20in%20another%20chariot.%20Then%20they%20brought%20him%20back%20to%20Jerusalem%2C%20where%20he%20died.%20He%20was%20buried%20there%20in%20the%20royal%20cemetery.%20And%20all%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem%20mourned%20for%20him.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_25%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20prophet%20Jeremiah%20composed%20funeral%20songs%20for%20Josiah%2C%20and%20to%20this%20day%20choirs%20still%20sing%20these%20sad%20songs%20about%20his%20death.%20These%20songs%20of%20sorrow%20have%20become%20a%20tradition%20and%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20Laments.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_26%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20of%20Josiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20and%20his%20acts%20of%20devotion%20(carried%20out%20according%20to%20what%20was%20written%20in%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E)%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_35_27%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2235%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3Efrom%20beginning%20to%20end%26%23x2014%3Ball%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Israel%20and%20Judah.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E36%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoahaz%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20people%20of%20the%20land%20took%20Josiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20son%20Jehoahaz%20and%20made%20him%20the%20next%20king%20in%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoahaz%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E36%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EJoahaz%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehoahaz%3B%20also%20in%2036%3A4.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20twenty-three%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20was%20deposed%20by%20the%20king%20of%20Egypt%2C%20who%20demanded%20that%20Judah%20pay%207%2C500%20pounds%20of%20silver%20and%2075%26%23xA0%3Bpounds%20of%20gold%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E36%3A3%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E100%26%23xA0%3Btalents%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B3%2C400%20kilograms%5D%20%3Cem%3Eof%20silver%20and%201%26%23xA0%3Btalent%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B34%26%23xA0%3Bkilograms%5D%20%3Cem%3Eof%20gold.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20as%20tribute.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoiakim%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20of%20Egypt%20then%20installed%20Eliakim%2C%20the%20brother%20of%20Jehoahaz%2C%20as%20the%20next%20king%20of%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem%2C%20and%20he%20changed%20Eliakim%26%23x2019%3Bs%20name%20to%20Jehoiakim.%20Then%20Neco%20took%20Jehoahaz%20to%20Egypt%20as%20a%20prisoner.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoiakim%20was%20twenty-five%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20eleven%20years.%20He%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20sight%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20his%20God.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%20of%20Babylon%20came%20to%20Jerusalem%20and%20captured%20it%2C%20and%20he%20bound%20Jehoiakim%20in%20bronze%20chains%20and%20led%20him%20away%20to%20Babylon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3ENebuchadnezzar%20also%20took%20some%20of%20the%20treasures%20from%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20and%20he%20placed%20them%20in%20his%20palace%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E36%3A7%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Etemple.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20in%20Babylon.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20in%20Jehoiakim%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20including%20all%20the%20evil%20things%20he%20did%20and%20everything%20found%20against%20him%2C%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Israel%20and%20Judah.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Then%20his%20son%20Jehoiachin%20became%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoiachin%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoiachin%20was%20eighteen%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E36%3A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20one%20Hebrew%20manuscript%2C%20some%20Greek%20manuscripts%2C%20and%20Syriac%20version%20(see%20also%202%26%23xA0%3BKgs%2024%3A8)%3B%20most%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20read%20%3Cem%3Eeight.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20three%20months%20and%20ten%20days.%20Jehoiachin%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20the%20spring%20of%20the%20year%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E36%3A10a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EAt%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20first%20day%20of%20this%20year%20in%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20was%20April%26%23xA0%3B13%2C%20597%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%20took%20Jehoiachin%20to%20Babylon.%20Many%20treasures%20from%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20were%20also%20taken%20to%20Babylon%20at%20that%20time.%20And%20Nebuchadnezzar%20installed%20Jehoiachin%26%23x2019%3Bs%20uncle%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E36%3A10b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20parallel%20text%20at%202%26%23xA0%3BKgs%2024%3A17%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Ebrother%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3Erelative.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Zedekiah%2C%20as%20the%20next%20king%20in%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EZedekiah%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EZedekiah%20was%20twenty-one%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20eleven%20years.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Zedekiah%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20sight%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20his%20God%2C%20and%20he%20refused%20to%20humble%20himself%20when%20the%20prophet%20Jeremiah%20spoke%20to%20him%20directly%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20also%20rebelled%20against%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%2C%20even%20though%20he%20had%20taken%20an%20oath%20of%20loyalty%20in%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20name.%20Zedekiah%20was%20a%20hard%20and%20stubborn%20man%2C%20refusing%20to%20turn%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2236%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3ELikewise%2C%20all%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20priests%20and%20the%20people%20became%20more%20and%20more%20unfaithful.%20They%20followed%20all%20the%20pagan%20practices%20of%20the%20surrounding%20nations%2C%20desecrating%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20that%20had%20been%20consecrated%20in%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_36_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20